HEADWORD: knowledge engineering
<hw>knowledge engineering</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The application of
computerized data and text manipulation to manage and interpret large
bodies of knowledge, or find useful information in large bodies of data.
The study of methods for knowledge engineering is generally considered
as a branch of <partof>artificial intelligence</partof>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>knowledge-intensive</ent>⟦br⟧
